text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia clandullensis is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is endemic to New South Wales.
The open pendulous shrub typically grows to a height of 1 to 2 metres (3 to 7 ft).It is mostly found in the areas around Clandulla and Glen Davis growing at higher altitudes in stony sandy or clay-loam soils where it is usually part of open Eucalyptus rossii woodland communities.
